to the editor re bilingual education on ballot in two states news article oct 9 susan mcgilvray rivet who oversees bilingual services in framingham mass says we can not expect everyone to learn at the same rate and then allow them to fail they need support in their native language i disagree forty years ago when i arrived in america with my non english speaking family my dad managed to learn english on his own so he could pass his driver 's license test and support us my brother and sisters and i went to public grammar school catholic high school and college all without the benefit of bilingual education and to preserve our heritage dad insisted that we speak our native ukrainian at home yet we managed to survive in the school system and as adults thrive in diverse careers we not only learned to speak english as children but we still speak ukrainian especially around mom and dad stephanie kostyk north caldwell nj oct 10 2002

